children.name: Text Description
children.characters: These are the standard drawer sizes and are used for when you need to provide detail about an item in the page context. Their size can be modified for your use case. Drawers have varios props including the abolity to overlay content or push content - see the docs for more detail on this

children.name: Text Description
children.characters: The full size draw is used when you have clicked on an action and require the user to be taken to a focussed workflow, and do not need page context.

children.name: Text Description
children.characters:
These base components are used in the drawer component, but are not intended to be used on their own. They will not be published to the
design system

children.name: This is a standard drawer header, it is used as a prefilled slot in the in context drawer - If you need something more custom, create a component in your local project and swap the component out.
